{"_id":"0xdxcUQkKDS0XbF2","name":"Macros for SWADE","content":"<h1>Macros for SWADE</h1>\n<p> </p>\n<h2><img src=\"icons/magic/symbols/rune-sigil-green.webp\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" /> Active Effect Builder</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Select or target some tokens. You can mix target and select.</li>\n<li>Type a desired name.</li>\n<li>Choose the AE type and define a value.</li>\n<li>All tokens will receive that active effect.</li>\n</ol>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Note 1: It will get the skill list only from the first selected token.</p>\n<p>Note 2: If you don't change the name it'll try to auto name the AE.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><img src=\"modules/swademacros/docs/aebuilder.webp\" width=\"452\" height=\"387\" /></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Notes</p>\n<ul>\n<li>It'll guess the best mode.</li>\n<li>true/false effects will always start true.</li>\n<li>Players can use this macro. Very useful for powers like this: @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.DPOBFvSuvQgDWF2c]{Protection}</li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<h2><img src=\"icons/sundries/gaming/playing-cards-grey.webp\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" /> Adventure Card</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Select one or more tokens.</li>\n<li>The Everyone option you give cards to all selected tokens. You can pick just one player.</li>\n<li>You need to choose the table with your adventure cards.</li>\n</ol>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Notes</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The player will receive a item (under gear) for each card. He can click on it to send to chat or open to see.</li>\n<li>If you create an additional stat called adventurecards the players can set the amount of cards they will receive.</li>\n<li>If didn't create the additional stat, the macro will read the rank. Novice = 1, etc.</li>\n<li>If you create an additional stat and did not have a rank that the macro can understand, the player will receive 1 card.</li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<p>About the Table</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The item created for the players will have the image in the table entry as the card and the text in the table as the item name.</li>\n<li>If you use the reset button this will reset the table and remove all cards from the tokens.</li>\n<li>You can set the default table in settings.</li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Create an Additional Stat</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swademacros.guide-macros-for-swade.PpSCLfufdR6THMeA]{Create an Additional Stat}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2><img src=\"icons/tools/scribal/magnifying-glass.webp\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" /> Character Summarizer</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>as a player, run the macro, it should summarise your char</li>\n<li>as a GM, run it, it should summarise all PCs</li>\n<li>as either, select a token and run it, it should summarise that char</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Discord for support: @penllawen </p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2><img src=\"icons/sundries/gaming/playing-cards.webp\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" /> Chase</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Run the macro.</li>\n<li>You can select a Deck. You can set to dogfight.</li>\n</ol>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Recommendations</p>\n<p>Create a table for chase. You can just duplicate the action cards table.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><img src=\"modules/swademacros/docs/chase.webp\" width=\"400\" height=\"333\" /></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Rules</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.nB1vsvPTn5jSRG6v]{Chases and Vehicles}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2><img src=\"icons/weapons/thrown/dynamite-simple-brown.webp\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" /> Deviation</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Run the macro and it will tell will where to land the template.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><img src=\"modules/swademacros/docs/deviation.webp\" width=\"286\" height=\"200\" /></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>You need to install:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/trioderegion/warpgate/releases/latest/download/module.json\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Warp Gate</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Rules</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.xxEcWExtn36PPxg0]{Area Effect Attacks}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2><img src=\"icons/commodities/tech/detonator-timer.webp\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" /> Dramatic Tasks</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Run the macro and choose how many players and the desired difficult.</li>\n<li>It'll whisper to you a suggestion.</li>\n</ol>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Rules</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.G9H6LoPoQu10TI4R]{Dramatic Tasks}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2><img src=\"icons/magic/death/undead-ghost-scream-teal.webp\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" /> Fear Table</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Select a token. Run the macro.</li>\n<li>You must select the fear source and the fear modifier.</li>\n<li>It'll test your spirit and check the result.</li>\n<li>Then it'll run Fear Table from the SWADE module. </li>\n<li>It'll try to apply some status.</li>\n</ol>\n<p> </p>\n<p><img src=\"modules/swademacros/docs/fear-macro.webp\" width=\"300\" height=\"176\" /></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Rules</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.jaYcLBJnBk1ai5EH]{Fear}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-tables.w4VswW37ksTmhngj]{Fear Table}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2><img src=\"icons/creatures/mammals/wolf-shadow-black.webp\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" /> Gang Up</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Select one token.</li>\n<li>Target another token.</li>\n<li>Run the macro. It'll calculate the Ganging Up bonus. </li>\n</ol>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Important</p>\n<p>This macro uses token disposition to indentify friend from foe. Be sure to set them property.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Module</p>\n<p>Token Faction is recommended.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Rules</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.hdXOHCe38O8KGyUz]{Ganging Up}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2><img src=\"icons/sundries/books/book-backed-blue-gold.webp\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" /> Interludes</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Select some tokens. They must have be linked and have an user.</li>\n</ol>\n<p> </p>\n<p>The macro will whisper for each token owner the interlude outcome.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Rules</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.fSBsmuTK9aYdGBsE]{Interludes}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2><img src=\"icons/environment/people/charge.webp\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" /> Mass Battle</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Run the macro.</li>\n<li>Fill the data.</li>\n<li>Battle!</li>\n</ol>\n<p> </p>\n<p><img src=\"modules/swademacros/docs/massbattle.webp\" width=\"280\" height=\"318\" /></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Rules</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.IJkWxV4kddDaU0Gl]{Mass Battles}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2><img src=\"icons/skills/movement/arrow-upward-yellow.webp\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" /> Raise Calculator</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Run the macro.</li>\n<li>It'll update the success level as you type.</li>\n</ol>\n<p> </p>\n<p><img src=\"modules/swademacros/docs/raisecalc.webp\" width=\"250\" height=\"163\" /></p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2><img src=\"icons/tools/hand/scale-balances-merchant-brown.webp\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" /> Size/Scale Calculator</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Select a token.</li>\n<li>Target another one.</li>\n<li>Run the macro.</li>\n</ol>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Rules</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.mbP0fwcquD98QtwX]{Size and Scale}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2><img src=\"icons/magic/symbols/elements-air-earth-fire-water.webp\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" /> Power Point Management</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Select a token and run the macro.</li>\n</ol>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Rules</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.6SGCG8rZNklN3U6w]{Recharging}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2><img src=\"icons/tools/nautical/steering-wheel.webp\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" /> Vehicle Maneuvers</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Run the macro.</li>\n</ol>\n<p> </p>\n<p>It's a macro for quick query rules.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Rules</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.nB1vsvPTn5jSRG6v]{Chases and Vehicles}</p>\n<p> </p>","img":"icons/sundries/gaming/playing-cards.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"tckKxzbezKvre3KI":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"26R0M4mnq6TPjaRs","name":"Alchemy","content":"<h1>Alchemy</h1>\n<p>You can search some items in the Items - Macros for SWADE compendium that will have a macro link in the description. </p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2>List</h2>\n<p>@Compendium[swademacros.items-for-macros.arDnD8BUiCDrZPZz]{Potion of Healing}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swademacros.items-for-macros.OXcHfuEV9mZMJPYJ]{Potion of Strong Healing}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swademacros.items-for-macros.L8Jurj2ICzHU1ISZ]{Potion of Invigoration}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swademacros.items-for-macros.XH42ILLDZbuEitMO]{Potion of Strong Invigoration}</p>","img":"icons/sundries/gaming/playing-cards.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"dJvi2seC8CqTkxhs":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.CO16N35lwnALPCc3"}}}
{"_id":"AhCtirFF3m2Qy1Oz","name":"Survival Guide","content":"<p><img style=\"border:0px;text-decoration:none;outline:none;display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto\" src=\"modules/swademacros/images/nottoday.webp\" width=\"300\" height=\"154\" /></p>\n<p> </p>\n<table style=\"height:512px;width:99.6506%;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height:17px\">\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:11.7144%;text-align:center\" colspan=\"2\"><strong>Problem:</strong></td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center;width:19.5118%;height:17px\" colspan=\"2\"><strong>And…</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width:12.0926%;height:17px;text-align:center\"><strong>Then Try To…</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width:45.5237%;height:17px;text-align:center\"><strong>Game Effect</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width:2.6695%;height:17px;text-align:center\"><strong>Helps:</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:21px\">\n<td style=\"height:359px;text-align:center;width:4.79839%\" rowspan=\"9\"><strong>You can’t hit the foe</strong></td>\n<td style=\"height:161px;text-align:center;width:6.91604%\" rowspan=\"4\"><strong>High Parry</strong></td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center;width:19.5118%;height:55px\" colspan=\"2\">Your team outnumbers the foe</td>\n<td style=\"width:12.0926%;height:55px;text-align:center\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.hdXOHCe38O8KGyUz]{Ganging Up}</td>\n<td style=\"width:45.5237%;height:55px;text-align:center\">\n<p>+1 Fighting for each additional non-Stunned ally in melee with the target (max +4).</p>\n<p>Lower this bonus by 1 point for every enemy adjacent to the target (min 0).</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"width:2.6695%;height:55px;text-align:center\">Team</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:17px\">\n<td style=\"text-align:center;width:19.5118%;height:55px\" colspan=\"2\">You are pretty strong (high Strength), you can move before acting and/or you have a shield</td>\n<td style=\"width:12.0926%;height:55px;text-align:center\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.GsNwqTjOQLVbQras]{Push} to knock them  @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.JhBfyamFYWMA4T93]{Prone}</td>\n<td style=\"width:45.5237%;height:55px;text-align:center\">\n<p>Opposed Strength or Athletic (each one chooses) roll (+2 if moved 2” before pushing, +Shield Parry Bonus): push 1”, 2” with a raise.</p>\n<p>The foe also rolls Athletics (-2 if the pusher raised) to avoid falling PRONE.</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"width:2.6695%;height:55px;text-align:center\">Team</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:17px\">\n<td style=\"text-align:center;width:19.5118%;height:17px\" colspan=\"2\">You are OK with lowering your defense</td>\n<td style=\"width:12.0926%;height:17px;text-align:center\">Do a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.iGSH4rtlKNSlJJff]{Wild Attack}</td>\n<td style=\"width:45.5237%;height:17px;text-align:center\">+2 Fighting, +2 melee damage, but you are now VULNERABLE</td>\n<td style=\"width:2.6695%;height:17px;text-align:center\">You</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:17px\">\n<td style=\"text-align:center;width:19.5118%;height:34px\" colspan=\"2\">You are using a melee weapon</td>\n<td style=\"width:12.0926%;height:34px;text-align:center\">Switch to RANGED ATTACKS</td>\n<td style=\"width:45.5237%;height:34px;text-align:center\">An enemy without COVER or similar has a target number of 4 to be hit by a ranged attack. Change up to 2 weapons as a free action once per turn.</td>\n<td style=\"width:2.6695%;height:34px;text-align:center\">You</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:34px\">\n<td style=\"text-align:center;width:6.91604%;height:68px\" rowspan=\"2\"><strong>Great Penalties for a Ranged Attack</strong></td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center;width:19.5118%;height:34px\" colspan=\"2\">You can miss a turn and you can stand still in your position</td>\n<td style=\"width:12.0926%;text-align:center;height:34px\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fxh6qdmOiHPAO0VK]{Aim}</td>\n<td style=\"width:45.5237%;text-align:center;height:34px\">Spend the entire turn (movement included) to lower by up to 4 points of penalties (from COVER, CALLED SHOT, Range…) OR add +2 to the first ranged attack of the next round.</td>\n<td style=\"width:2.6695%;text-align:center;height:34px\">You</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:34px\">\n<td style=\"text-align:center;width:19.5118%;height:34px\" colspan=\"2\">You are using a ranged weapon, and you can shorten the distance to engage in melee</td>\n<td style=\"width:12.0926%;text-align:center;height:34px\">Switch to MELEE ATTACKS</td>\n<td style=\"width:45.5237%;text-align:center;height:34px\">An enemy with COVER or PRONE can still be hit without penalties with Fighting. Change up to 2 weapons as a free action once per turn.</td>\n<td style=\"width:2.6695%;text-align:center;height:34px\">You</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:17px\">\n<td style=\"text-align:center;height:130px;width:6.91604%\" rowspan=\"3\"><strong>One of the motives above, or both</strong></td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center;width:19.5118%;height:34px\" colspan=\"2\">You can help an ally (“he has a weak spot there!”, trip the foe, “JUST DO IT!”)</td>\n<td style=\"width:12.0926%;text-align:center;height:34px\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.TFR8EmfT9ci1gBEy]{Support} an ally’s combat skill</td>\n<td style=\"width:45.5237%;text-align:center;height:34px\">Describe how you help your ally’s Trait and roll your relevant Skill to give them +1 with a success, +2 with a raise (max +4).</td>\n<td style=\"width:2.6695%;text-align:center;height:34px\">Ally</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:17px\">\n<td style=\"text-align:center;width:19.5118%;height:79px\" colspan=\"2\">You can hinder your foe through a clever tactic (throw sand in their eyes, a feint, ”look behind you”, provocations, war cries)</td>\n<td style=\"width:12.0926%;text-align:center;height:79px\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.2aAyYC6n07MrZ47O]{Test} your foe to make them  @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.vuud75GDkKL3NW10]{Distracted and Vulnerable}</td>\n<td style=\"width:45.5237%;text-align:center;height:79px\">\n<p>Describe a TEST and roll a relevant Skill against the foe’s linked Attribute.</p>\n<p>Success: the foe is DISTRACTED or VULNERABLE, your choice.</p>\n<p>Raise: the foe is also SHAKEN.</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"width:2.6695%;text-align:center;height:79px\">Team</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:17px\">\n<td style=\"text-align:center;width:19.5118%;height:17px\" colspan=\"2\">You are OK with sacrificing your movement</td>\n<td style=\"width:12.0926%;text-align:center;height:17px\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.od3tHNJTS8Ma4n2o]{GRAPPLE} your foe</td>\n<td style=\"width:45.5237%;text-align:center;height:17px\">\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.sTArFBzbesQkjLVg]{Bound and Entangled}</p>\n<p>Athletics (or Strength -2) vs Athletics (or Strength -2) to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.sTArFBzbesQkjLVg]{ENTANGLE}the target, or to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.sTArFBzbesQkjLVg]{BOUND} (the grappler is also VULNERABLE) with a raise.</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"width:2.6695%;text-align:center;height:17px\">Team</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:17px\">\n<td style=\"text-align:center;height:51px;width:11.7144%\" colspan=\"2\" rowspan=\"2\"><strong>You can’t damage the foe enough (High Toughness*)</strong></td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center;width:19.5118%;height:34px\" colspan=\"2\">You aren’t having problems hitting the foe</td>\n<td style=\"width:12.0926%;text-align:center;height:34px\">Do a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.OpzGhU3fssihv5ds]{CALLED SHOT} against a weak point</td>\n<td style=\"width:45.5237%;text-align:center;height:34px\">Limb: -2 (may @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.GkQ6WX0VSFHdTS3N]{Disarm}; Hand: -4 (may @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.GkQ6WX0VSFHdTS3N]{Disarm}), Head/Vitals: -4 (+4 damage), Unarmored Area: -? (damage ignores Armor).</td>\n<td style=\"width:2.6695%;text-align:center;height:34px\">You</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:17px\">\n<td style=\"text-align:center;width:19.5118%;height:17px\" colspan=\"2\">You are OK with lowering your defense</td>\n<td style=\"width:12.0926%;text-align:center;height:17px\">Do a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.iGSH4rtlKNSlJJff]{Wild Attack}</td>\n<td style=\"width:45.5237%;text-align:center;height:17px\">+2 Fighting, +2 melee damage, but you are now VULNERABLE</td>\n<td style=\"width:2.6695%;text-align:center;height:17px\">You</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:17px\">\n<td style=\"text-align:center;height:85px;width:11.7144%\" colspan=\"2\" rowspan=\"4\"><strong>You are going to die soon if you keep standing there!</strong></td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center;width:19.5118%;height:17px\" colspan=\"2\">You are engaged in melee and you don’t want to risk rolling your dice</td>\n<td style=\"width:12.0926%;text-align:center;height:17px\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.qfAkQVB9LbFFdDQ3]{WITHDRAW} WITHDRAW to fight another day!</td>\n<td style=\"width:45.5237%;text-align:center;height:17px\">Each non-Shaken and non-Stunned adjacent enemy receives a free attack against the hero that flees from melee. You may use your turn to DEFEND (see pag. 100) in order to gain +4 Parry and move your normal Pace (but not run).</td>\n<td style=\"width:2.6695%;text-align:center;height:17px\">You</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:17px\">\n<td style=\"text-align:center;width:10.2335%;height:34px\" rowspan=\"2\">You are engaged by a single enemy…</td>\n<td style=\"width:9.2783%;text-align:center;height:17px\">…but you are pretty Strong (high Strength) and/or you have a shield</td>\n<td style=\"width:12.0926%;text-align:center;height:17px\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.GsNwqTjOQLVbQras]{Push} to make your foe non adjacent, then move</td>\n<td style=\"width:45.5237%;text-align:center;height:17px\">Opposed Strength or Athletic (each one chooses) roll ( +Shield Parry Bonus): push 1”, 2” with a raise. The foe also rolls Athletics (-2 if the pusher raised) to avoid falling PRONE.</td>\n<td style=\"width:2.6695%;text-align:center;height:17px\">You, Team</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:17px\">\n<td style=\"width:9.2783%;text-align:center;height:17px\">…but you can hinder your foe through a clever tactic</td>\n<td style=\"width:12.0926%;text-align:center;height:17px\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.2aAyYC6n07MrZ47O]{Test} to make your foe @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.vuud75GDkKL3NW10]{Distracted and Vulnerable} or even SHAKEN, then move</td>\n<td style=\"width:45.5237%;text-align:center;height:17px\">\n<p>Describe a TEST and roll a relevant Skill against the foe’s linked Attribute.</p>\n<p>Success: the foe is DISTRACTED or VULNERABLE, your choice.</p>\n<p>Raise: the foe is also SHAKEN.</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"width:2.6695%;text-align:center;height:17px\">You, Team</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:34px\">\n<td style=\"text-align:center;width:19.5118%;height:34px\" colspan=\"2\">The foes target you from afar</td>\n<td style=\"width:12.0926%;text-align:center;height:34px\">Find @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.854By7DpYevCCEfJ]{Cover and Obstacles} or move then drop @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.JhBfyamFYWMA4T93]{Prone}</td>\n<td style=\"width:45.5237%;text-align:center;height:34px\">Attackers subtract from -2 to -8 to their ranged attacks against you, depending on the COVER you found, PRONE is a -4 COVER against ranged attacks from 3”+.</td>\n<td style=\"width:2.6695%;text-align:center;height:34px\">You</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p> </p>\n<p>*Many of the combat maneuvers that assist in hitting a foe also help deal damage, as they increase the chance of getting a raise and extra +1d6 damage (or they make an opponent SHAKEN).</p>\n<p> </p>\n<ul>\n<li>RECOVER from being SHAKEN: Roll Spirit at the start of your turn, or spend a Benny at any time (pag. 94).</li>\n<li>SOAK incoming Wounds: Spend a Benny and roll Vigor to negate one wound for every success and raise (pag. 96).</li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<ul>\n<li>BOUND: Cannot move, cannot do other physical actions except trying to break free, DISTRACTED and VULNERABLE as long as they remain Bound. Use an action to roll Athletics (or Strength -2) and become ENTANGLED with a success, or break free with a raise (p. 98).</li>\n<li>DISTRACTED: -2 to the character’s roll until the end of their next turn (p. 100).</li>\n<li>ENTANGLED: Cannot move and is DISTRACTED as long as they remain Entangled. Use an action to roll Athletics (or Strength -2) and break free (p. 98).</li>\n<li>PRONE: -2 Parry, -2 Fighting, -4 to be hit from range 3”+ (doesn’t stack with COVER), -4 damage from attack with Area of Effects, use 2” of Pace to crawl 1” or to stand up (p. 104).</li>\n<li>SHAKEN: Can only perform free actions (including normal movement, plus eventually running). Recover from being SHAKEN as free action with a Spirit roll at the start of the character’s turn (p. 94).</li>\n<li>STUNNED: Can’t move nor take actions, is PRONE, attacks against him get THE DROP (p. 100). Each turn make a Vigor roll to recover: success recovers but is DISTRACTED and VULNERABLE, raise no ill effects.</li>\n<li>VULNERABLE: +2 to every roll against them until the end of their next turn (pag. 100).</li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<p>by u/anri11, Silent Mask</p>","img":"icons/sundries/gaming/playing-cards.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"tckKxzbezKvre3KI":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"B3gVnp8czFI7DZk3","name":"_READ THIS","content":"<h1>Instructions</h1>\n<p> </p>\n<h2>First Time</h2>\n<p>You only need to import the macros from the <strong>Auto Update Macros</strong> compendium.</p>\n<p>To do that right click the compendium and click <strong>Import All Content</strong>.</p>\n<p>Now, after each update for the Macros for SWADE module your macros will be updated.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2>New Macros</h2>\n<p>If a new macro were uploaded you can check it out in the compendium <strong>Auto Update Macros</strong>. You can right click the macro and click <strong>Import Entry</strong>.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2>Old Users</h2>\n<p>If you imported the macros from the compendium Macros for SWADE you'll have to delete the old macro and import the newer version for each update. This is not recommended because it's very boring.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2>Private Compendiums</h2>\n<p>The compendiums with macros from this module are <strong>private</strong> by default. You need to choose to import the macros for the players. </p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2>Incompatibility</h2>\n<p>This module won't work with:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/League-of-Foundry-Developers/fvtt-advanced-macros\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Advanced Macros</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<h2>Requirements</h2>\n<p>You need to install:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/trioderegion/warpgate/releases/latest/download/module.json\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Warp Gate</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<h2>Documentation</h2>\n<p>@Compendium[swademacros.guide-macros-for-swade.dyHC5k4Tlah2dAek]{Everyday Macros}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swademacros.guide-macros-for-swade.Gxe7Suuu2hfKM7j0]{Macros for Players}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swademacros.guide-macros-for-swade.WkRZaEEGuCSSqp5R]{Macros for Settings}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swademacros.guide-macros-for-swade.0xdxcUQkKDS0XbF2]{Macros for SWADE}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swademacros.guide-macros-for-swade.lWtA4s31kzgkF1qt]{Special Macros}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swademacros.guide-macros-for-swade.26R0M4mnq6TPjaRs]{Alchemy}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<h1>Tips</h1>\n<p> </p>\n<h2>Modules</h2>\n<p>There is a list with a couple of modules I recommend to use with these macros.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Combat Utility Belt</p>\n<p>This module can make conditions useful with the Condition Lab feature.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Macro Folders</p>\n<p>This can make very easy to share a folder with macros for the players.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Permission Viewer</p>\n<p>You need to know what macros will be shared with the players. This module helps with that.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Turn Alert</p>\n<p>You can set alerts for the combat. The power ends after rounds. The target is stunned until the end of its next turn.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>","img":"icons/sundries/gaming/playing-cards.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"tckKxzbezKvre3KI":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"Gxe7Suuu2hfKM7j0","name":"Macros for Players","content":"<h1>Macros for Players</h1>\n<p> </p>\n<h2><img src=\"icons/magic/movement/chevrons-down-yellow.webp\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" /> Boost/Lower Trait</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Target one or more tokens. </li>\n<li>Select if you want to boost or lower a trait. </li>\n</ol>\n<p> </p>\n<h2><img src=\"icons/magic/time/arrows-circling-pink.webp\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" /> Equip/Unequip Set</h2>\n<p>You can create two sets of items that can be swapped. Example: You have a crossbow (set 1) and a sword and shield. You can execute the macro to change between them. </p>\n<ol>\n<li>Open your actor sheet.</li>\n<li>You need to add to <strong>Description</strong> of the items <strong>#equipSet1</strong> or <strong>#equipSet2</strong>. Capitalization matter.</li>\n<li>When you run the macro it will equip set one and disable set two and if you execute again it will reverse this.</li>\n</ol>\n<p> </p>\n<h2><img src=\"icons/magic/life/cross-area-circle-green-white.webp\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" /> Healing</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Select a token. Run the macro.</li>\n<li>Natural Healing and Skill Healing</li>\n</ol>\n<p> </p>\n<p>You can select and target a token. If you do this, the roll for Skill Healing will not heal the selected token. It'll tell about a attempt to heal the target.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Rules</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.gCrNh35pUQHaVN4J]{Healing}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2><img src=\"icons/sundries/books/book-embossed-spiral-purple-white.webp\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" /> Spellbook Manager</h2>\n<p>You can create three sets of powers that can be swapped. Example: You have a Bolt, Confusion (set 1), Healing and Confusion (set 2). You can execute the macro to change between them. </p>\n<ol>\n<li>Open your actor sheet.</li>\n<li>You need to add to <strong>Description</strong> of the powers <strong>#</strong><strong>spellBook1</strong>,<strong> </strong><strong>#</strong><strong>spellBook2 </strong>or <strong>#spellBook3</strong>. Capitalization matter.</li>\n<li>When you run the macro it will equip set one and disable set two and if you execute again it will reverse this.</li>\n</ol>\n<p> </p>\n<h2><img src=\"icons/skills/social/diplomacy-unity-alliance.webp\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" /> Support</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Select a token and target another one.</li>\n<li>You can now select a skill to support and check out the target skill list.</li>\n</ol>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Rules</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.TFR8EmfT9ci1gBEy]{Support}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2><img src=\"icons/sundries/gaming/dice-pair-white-green.webp\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" /> Test</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Select a token and target another one. Run the macro.</li>\n<li>If you check the Creative Combat box, it'll run the table for you.</li>\n</ol>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Rules</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.2aAyYC6n07MrZ47O]{Test}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.c8c42DBDAA7zmFhE]{Creative Combat}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2><img src=\"icons/magic/control/fear-fright-white.webp\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" /> Unshaken</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Select a token.</li>\n<li>Run the macro.</li>\n<li>If the token is shaken it will offer to roll spirit and spend a benny on failure.</li>\n<li>If the token is unshaken it will set the Shaken status to it.</li>\n</ol>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Rules</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.30TJKevSbgxK6jQy]{Damage Effects}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2><img src=\"icons/magic/symbols/symbol-lightning-bolt.webp\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" /> Unstun</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Select a token.</li>\n<li>Run the macro.</li>\n<li>If the token is stunned it will offer to roll vigor and spend a benny on failure.</li>\n<li>If the token is unstunned it will set the stunned status to it.</li>\n</ol>\n<p> </p>\n<p>If you set the Combat Utility Belt condition for prone, it'll mark it too.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Rules</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.nHbnnGpaM8CgA5SI]{Stunned}</p>","img":"icons/sundries/gaming/playing-cards.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"8A8MXeQUcdCXOOtn":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swademacros.guide-macros-for-swade.AhCtirFF3m2Qy1Oz"}}}
{"name":"Create an Additional Stat","content":"<h1>Additional Stats</h1>\n<p>You can create extra fields the actor sheet or in the items.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Go to Configure Settings.</li>\n<li>Click System Settings </li>\n<li>Click Open Setting Configurator.</li>\n<li>Scroll down until Additional Stats.</li>\n<li>Add one to actors or items. You can pick some kinds of fields. Number, Text, etc.</li>\n<li>Save it.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><img src=\"modules/swademacros/docs/aditionalstats1.webp\" width=\"568\" height=\"800\" /></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Now you need to activate it for each actor sheet or item. </p>\n<ol>\n<li>Click in Tweaks in the actor sheet or item sheet.</li>\n<li>Check enable for the Additional Stat you want.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><img src=\"modules/swademacros/docs/aditionalstats2.webp\" width=\"384\" height=\"726\" /></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>","img":"icons/sundries/gaming/playing-cards.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"8A8MXeQUcdCXOOtn":3},"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"teste-savageworlds","system":"swade","coreVersion":"0.8.9","systemVersion":"0.21.3"},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.EzbU7KCX3HsxGZDr"}},"_id":"PpSCLfufdR6THMeA"}
{"_id":"WkRZaEEGuCSSqp5R","name":"Macros for Settings","content":"<p> </p>\n<h1>Deadlands</h1>\n<p> </p>\n<h2><img src=\"modules/deadlands-core-rules/assets/icons/deadlands-logo.webp\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" /> Adventure Generator</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Run the macro.</li>\n<li>It'll show the possible adventure in the chat. If you liked it, you can click the button to create a Journal with it. Do not require to import the tables.</li>\n</ol>\n<p> </p>\n<h1>Sprawlrunners</h1>\n<p> </p>\n<h2><img src=\"icons/commodities/treasure/puzzle-box-glowing-blue.webp\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" /> LP Check</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Run the macro.</li>\n<li>All players with a character selected will have their Logistics Points accounted from the itens.</li>\n</ol>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>Important</strong></p>\n<p>The item must be equipped or it'll not count.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Requirements</p>\n<p>You must set Additional Stats in System Settings like the image:</p>\n<p><img src=\"modules/swademacros/docs/sprawllpcheck.webp\" width=\"600\" height=\"547\" /></p>\n<p>Then, you must enable it in the Actor Sheet.</p>\n<p><img src=\"modules/swademacros/docs/sprawllpcheck2.webp\" width=\"625\" height=\"697\" /></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Sprawlrunners--FoundryVTT-Module</p>\n<p>https://www.drivethrurpg.com/product/351063/Sprawlrunners--FoundryVTT-Module</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Rule</p>\n<p>@Compendium[sprawl-core-rules.sprawl-rules.jhEs3al7qA4sAwaa]{Logistics Points}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2><img src=\"icons/commodities/tech/antenna-powered-purple.webp\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" /> Cyberspace Actions</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Run the macro.</li>\n<li>The player must choose 1 action only. It'll send to the chat the action.</li>\n</ol>\n<p> </p>\n<p><img src=\"modules/swademacros/docs/cyberspaceactions.png\" width=\"300\" height=\"279\" /></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Rules</p>\n<p>@Compendium[sprawl-core-rules.sprawl-rules.YlzlYF4w9OiFgHTG]{Cyberspace Actions}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2><img src=\"icons/commodities/currency/coins-plain-gold.webp\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" /> Coin Manager for Savage Pathfinder</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Select one or more tokens and run the macro.</li>\n<li>You can add or remove coins from the selected token.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Notes</p>\n<ul>\n<li>This macro will create the items on the tokens.</li>\n<li>The tokens must be a linked token.</li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>","img":"icons/sundries/gaming/playing-cards.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"tckKxzbezKvre3KI":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"dyHC5k4Tlah2dAek","name":"Everyday Macros","content":"<h1>Macros for SWADE</h1>\n<p> </p>\n<h2>Macro Managers</h2>\n<p>You can use the managers to open a menu with the main macros for each role. It'll only work after you import all macros.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>You can change the macros that will appear in the manager by switching the names by the ones you desire.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>  const macros = [</p>\n<p>    \"Macro 1\",</p>\n<p>    \"Macro 2\"</p>\n<p>  ];</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p> </p>\n<p>GM - Macro Manager</p>\n<p><img src=\"modules/swademacros/docs/gmmacromanager.webp\" width=\"250\" height=\"169\" /></p>\n<p>Player - Macro Manager</p>\n<p><img src=\"modules/swademacros/docs/playermacromanager.webp\" width=\"250\" height=\"132\" /></p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2><img src=\"icons/tools/navigation/sextant-steel-blue.webp\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" /> 3D Measure</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Select a token and target other tokens. </li>\n<li>It'll display to the chat the distance between then calculating <strong>height</strong>.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><img src=\"modules/swademacros/docs/%203dMeasure.webp\" width=\"400\" height=\"349\" /></p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2><img src=\"icons/magic/time/arrows-circling-pink.webp\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" /> Next Turn</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>It'll skip the current turn if are in combat.</li>\n</ol>\n<p> </p>\n<h2><img src=\"icons/magic/time/clock-stopwatch-white-blue.webp\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" /> Quick Combat</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Run the macro.</li>\n<li>It'll select ALL tokens in the active scene, send them to combat tracker.</li>\n</ol>\n<p> </p>\n<p>You can now mount the groups. Then press Begin Combat.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2><img src=\"icons/sundries/lights/torch-brown-lit.webp\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" /> Token Vision</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Select one or more tokens and run the macro.</li>\n<li>A player can use this macro to change the light source. A GM can change light source and vision type.</li>\n</ol>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>","img":"icons/sundries/gaming/playing-cards.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"tckKxzbezKvre3KI":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"lWtA4s31kzgkF1qt","name":"Special Macros","content":"<h2>Special Macros</h2>\n<p> </p>\n<h2><img src=\"icons/tools/navigation/map-chart-tan.webp\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" /> Feet To SWADE</h2>\n<blockquote>\n<p><strong>DO NOT USE THIS MACRO UNLESS YOU KNOW WHAT YOU DOING</strong></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>This macro will read the active scene and change the size of wall lights. <strong>THIS CAN'T BE UNDONE</strong>. </p>\n<p>If you install any map from foundry it'll came with 5 ft square and the lights set to this. This macro will fix the lights for you. You should duplicate a scene before run this.</p>\n<p><img src=\"modules/swademacros/docs/feettoswade01.webp\" width=\"600\" height=\"423\" /></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><img src=\"modules/swademacros/docs/feettoswade02.webp\" width=\"600\" height=\"360\" /></p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2><img src=\"icons/sundries/gaming/rune-card.webp\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" /> Images To Folder</h2>\n<p>This macro will read all images in a folder and create a journal with each image inside a folder in the journal tab.</p>\n<p>It's useful for:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>create your own action deck</li>\n<li>create an adventure deck</li>\n<li>add lots of image handouts</li>\n</ul>\n<p>For action deck you can just export the folder to a compendium and click <strong>Open in Action Card Editor</strong>.</p>\n<p><img src=\"modules/swademacros/docs/imagestofolder01.webp\" width=\"600\" height=\"490\" /></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>1. Run the macro.</p>\n<p><img src=\"modules/swademacros/docs/imagestofolder02.webp\" width=\"300\" height=\"203\" /></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>","img":"icons/sundries/gaming/playing-cards.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"tckKxzbezKvre3KI":3},"flags":{}}
